Patent on collaboratively building dashboards in real-time across multiple machines. 

Abstract: A computer system facilitates the collaborative design and presentation of graphical dashboard displays or the like by initiating the presentation of dashboard imagery on each of the collaborating system displays. When a user of a client system identifies an object of the dashboard display for editing, instructions are sent to each of the other collaborating systems to identify the editing party and to prevent simultaneous edits of the same object by multiple parties. Edited objects may be shaded, colored or otherwise highlighted to provide additional information about the editor, the changes being made or the like.
included.title: Computing systems and processes for simultaneous co-development of dashboard interfaces.

included.description:
Post-grad position as a Interaction Design Trainee in the highly competitive Huge UX School program in Brooklyn, NY. With a focus on UI in college I felt that diving deep into UX would help me round out my skills as a designer. 

â¢ While at Huge I have learned to appreciate the fine art of carefully balancing user needs and business goals to create products that improve life for the people who use them. 

â¢ I was fortunate to be given hands on training sessions and feedback by Huge's experienced Interaction Designers and members of several other disciplines within the company. 

â¢ I discovered a passion and appreciation for UX best practices, prototyping, meticulous wireframing, information architecture, user research, user testing, user personas and scenarios.

Huge has greatly strengthen my resolve to become a product designer.
